This paper is about a new architecture for automatic speech recognition (ASR) that utilizes both acoustic and symbolic input. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the categories of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Sound (cs.SD), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses different ways of transforming large text corpora, which suggests that it could also belong to the categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
